  "title": "Lesson 14",
  "topic": "The Future Tense",
  "grammar": {
    "explanations": [
      "The future tense is formed by adding -ssa to the root or verbal base with, or in some cases without, the connecting vowel -i-. The terminations are the same as those in the present tense.",
      "Attention may be paid to the following irregular future forms: gacchati → gamissati (he will go), āgacchati → āgamissati (he will come), dadāti → dadissati / dassati (he will give), tiṭṭhati → ṭhassati (he will stand), karoti → karissati (he will do)."
    ],
